1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,165
< That my mother was pushed down by Yume

2
00:00:07,165 --> 00:00:08,825
Mio I don't know>

3
00:00:08,825 --> 00:00:12,033
(Mio) I guess it was my fault after all.

4
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:14,825
< The way she looks forward to accept her mother's death

5
00:00:14,825 --> 00:00:18,693
Yume strengthens her resolve to keep her secret secret>

6
00:00:18,693 --> 00:00:22,033
📱(Sakura) If you don't pay me 1 million yen, I'll give you everything.

7
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:26,627
<Will the fate of this forbidden friendship be hope or destruction...>

8
00:00:31,363 --> 00:00:33,033
welcome

9
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:36,099
Okay, okay, I don't have time anymore.

10
00:00:36,099 --> 00:00:38,033
(Misato) Please tell me how much you are now.

11
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:40,594
That's the one who said "Welcome"

12
00:00:42,957 --> 00:00:45,528
Ah, hey, it's okay to be normal.

13
00:00:45,528 --> 00:00:48,561
Yeah? If it's okay to be normal

14
00:00:48,561 --> 00:00:51,330
It turns out that you don't have to set it.

15
00:00:51,330 --> 00:00:53,000
Don't get too excited

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:59,330
Hey, do you want to turn around your face? It's Korean style

17
00:00:59,330 --> 00:01:01,462
I'm not saying that just the set is enough.

18
00:01:01,462 --> 00:01:04,660
(Misato) Yes, customer, don't move.

19
00:01:06,231 --> 00:01:10,462
Is it your colleague's wedding?

20
00:01:10,462 --> 00:01:14,297
His only colleague left Kotobuki.

21
00:01:14,297 --> 00:01:16,528
Hmm

22
00:01:17,726 --> 00:01:22,825
What about the customers? Don't you have any plans to get married?

23
00:01:22,825 --> 00:01:25,660
Ah... nothing in particular.

24
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:30,693
Why, even though she has a cute face, she ignores my eyes.

25
00:01:30,693 --> 00:01:33,066
It's not like, "Why?" This is a story like this.

26
00:01:33,066 --> 00:01:38,033
Yes customer doesn't move hehehe

27
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:41,198
What is your job? Is everything going well?

28
00:01:41,198 --> 00:01:44,825
Ah well yes normally

29
00:01:44,825 --> 00:01:50,627
Hmm, I've been thinking that for a while, but what?

30
00:01:50,627 --> 00:01:55,759
Why is it a squid when it's a horse?

31
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:57,858
I understand if it's horse meat.

32
00:01:57,858 --> 00:01:59,891
Huh?

33
00:01:59,891 --> 00:02:04,363
You and this president's name are Umada, right?

34
00:02:04,363 --> 00:02:08,066
But why does the horse sell squid?

35
00:02:08,066 --> 00:02:10,264
Huh?

36
00:02:10,264 --> 00:02:13,231
He's a child of that company.

37
00:02:13,231 --> 00:02:18,594
I wonder if the gift is salted squid? That can't be true, right?

38
00:02:18,594 --> 00:02:22,429
You and this salted fish are quite delicious.

39
00:02:22,429 --> 00:02:26,132
I want to eat salted fish

40
00:02:26,132 --> 00:02:33,231
I hope everything goes well, but...

41
00:02:33,231 --> 00:02:36,891
It's okay if you quit altogether.

42
00:02:36,891 --> 00:02:41,627
Huh? (Misato) If work is boring

43
00:02:43,561 --> 00:02:49,495
(Misato) I don't think age matters when it comes to finding what you like.

44
00:02:55,297 --> 00:02:59,924
Did your mother like being a hairdresser?

45
00:02:59,924 --> 00:03:02,759
(Misato) That's right.

46
00:03:02,759 --> 00:03:05,825
So why did you suddenly close the shop?

47
00:03:06,825 --> 00:03:11,924
That's because... no customers come.

48
00:03:11,924 --> 00:03:13,594
yes done

49
00:03:16,066 --> 00:03:19,165
Oh, what about ophthalmology? Are you okay now?

50
00:03:19,165 --> 00:03:23,726
(Misato) Huh? Are you talking about when?

51
00:03:27,495 --> 00:03:30,297
Mom, were you happy?

52
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,825
yeah? what?

53
00:03:35,825 --> 00:03:39,099
that's why…

54
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:43,759
My mother has been working ever since my father died...

55
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:49,132
(hair dryer sound)

56
00:03:49,132 --> 00:03:53,099
Sorry, I couldn't hear you at all. What?

57
00:03:56,330 --> 00:03:58,330
Let's go eat sometime next time

58
00:03:58,330 --> 00:04:04,429
(Misato) Huh? It doesn't matter, you're busy too.

59
00:04:04,429 --> 00:04:07,660
It's okay, but sometimes

60
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:11,000
(Misato) Is it horse meat? Huh?

61
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,165
(Misato) Or squid? Hehehehe

62
00:04:17,165 --> 00:04:18,858
Thank you, that was helpful

63
00:04:18,858 --> 00:04:23,858
Ah! Collar... Huh?

64
00:04:23,858 --> 00:04:27,858
No, I just can't find the words anymore.

65
00:04:29,363 --> 00:04:33,297
Necklace Hehe, the collar was often used in reverse.

66
00:04:33,297 --> 00:04:35,825
(Misato) The pearl one seems to go well with it.

67
00:04:35,825 --> 00:04:39,825
I've been meaning to give it to you for a while now.

68
00:04:39,825 --> 00:04:41,891
I wonder where it went... Ah, good, good, good!

69
00:04:41,891 --> 00:04:43,891
Sorry, I really don't have time today.

70
00:04:43,891 --> 00:04:48,924
Is it pearl? The tall one is cute

71
00:04:48,924 --> 00:04:51,726
Even if it's expensive or cute, I don't have time

72
00:04:51,726 --> 00:04:55,066
Ah yes... I'll contact you again.

73
00:04:56,363 --> 00:04:59,792
Hey?

74
00:04:59,792 --> 00:05:06,891
Gift: If it's really salted fish, give it to me, hehehehe

75
00:05:10,231 --> 00:05:30,231
♬〜

76
00:05:30,231 --> 00:05:34,000
♬〜

77
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:04,957
(Yume) Will the bottom fall out? Huh?

78
00:06:04,957 --> 00:06:08,132
No, that's not straight.

79
00:06:08,132 --> 00:06:11,363
I'm sorry.

80
00:06:11,363 --> 00:06:14,693
The basics are cross stitching, so yes, I understand, I understand.

81
00:06:14,693 --> 00:06:18,429
I'll put heavy things in this small box.

82
00:06:18,429 --> 00:06:20,825
Is it pasted on the letter K?

83
00:06:20,825 --> 00:06:23,363
No, if you do this, it will look like the katakana ``ki''.

84
00:06:23,363 --> 00:06:25,462
what? A pun? Something like a letter “K”

85
00:06:25,462 --> 00:06:28,462
I've never heard of it (sigh)

86
00:06:28,462 --> 00:06:31,924
Sometimes when I don't have common sense, what's that?

87
00:06:31,924 --> 00:06:34,528
Sorry, my mouth spoke on its own.

88
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:37,528
Hey, that theory that you just said on your own.

89
00:06:37,528 --> 00:06:41,099
Won't you please stop? Your mouth won't speak on its own.

90
00:06:41,099 --> 00:06:43,528
Is it your frontal lobe that says let's talk?

91
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:45,198
For now, your brain...

92
00:06:45,198 --> 00:06:47,858
Why are you so fluent?

93
00:06:47,858 --> 00:06:50,198
Okay, okay, okay, okay, if you're going to say that much.

94
00:06:50,198 --> 00:06:52,660
I'll ask Champy, okay?

95
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:55,726
I've been friends with you longer than you, so Nekotora

96
00:06:56,792 --> 00:06:58,693
(AI startup sound) That's right.

97
00:06:58,693 --> 00:07:01,693
Do you know the correct way to assemble cardboard?

98
00:07:01,693 --> 00:07:03,429
(AI voice) “When assembling cardboard

99
00:07:03,429 --> 00:07:05,231
The basics are cross stitches.”

100
00:07:05,231 --> 00:07:09,297
"However, when putting heavy items in it, we recommend using the "K"-shaped sticker."

101
00:07:15,165 --> 00:07:19,198
Well then, these heavy books are in this box.

102
00:07:19,198 --> 00:07:21,660
Oh, that's no good, huh?

103
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:23,528
Because it's your mother's

104
00:07:23,528 --> 00:07:26,396
Come out the other day

105
00:07:26,396 --> 00:07:29,033
I didn't have the image of reading a book or anything.

106
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:31,099
I wonder what you're reading

107
00:07:31,099 --> 00:07:34,000
But this is my mom's, so I can't take it with me.

108
00:07:35,924 --> 00:07:40,297
It's a bit tricky, isn't it? What and how far can you take it?

109
00:07:40,297 --> 00:07:43,264
You can't do your mother's thing because you're disinheriting it.

110
00:07:43,264 --> 00:07:45,693
I know that.

111
00:07:45,693 --> 00:07:48,264
Basically from my previous apartment the other day.

112
00:07:48,264 --> 00:07:51,759
I guess I have the image of only bringing what I brought with me.

113
00:07:52,858 --> 00:07:54,528
Understood

114
00:07:56,957 --> 00:07:59,462
Thank you. That was helpful. See you soon.

115
00:07:59,462 --> 00:08:02,858
Oh, hey, hey, hey, Sunday, are you free? Would you like to eat at home?

116
00:08:02,858 --> 00:08:07,957
Huh? Look, I'm saying goodbye to this house.

117
00:08:07,957 --> 00:08:10,132
It's not about making memories before moving.

118
00:08:10,132 --> 00:08:12,495
Somehow

119
00:08:12,495 --> 00:08:16,165
Yeah, I understand. I'll save it on Sunday.

120
00:08:16,165 --> 00:08:19,066
I don't think I can paste the letter K. I can't paste the letter K.

121
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:23,000
(Sound of door opening and closing)

122
00:08:25,495 --> 00:08:34,957
♬〜

123
00:08:34,957 --> 00:08:40,396
(Sakura)16 17 18 19 20

124
00:08:40,396 --> 00:08:42,891
21 22 23…

125
00:08:42,891 --> 00:08:44,561
It's okay

126
00:08:44,561 --> 00:08:46,330
Ah, now I don't understand anymore

127
00:08:46,330 --> 00:08:48,924
Is it 26? 26 27…

128
00:08:48,924 --> 00:08:51,759
There's no way you're going to leave it to me like that now.

129
00:08:57,858 --> 00:09:02,693
Did you steal it from your parents? I didn't steal it

130
00:09:02,693 --> 00:09:07,297
So what? Bank robbery?

131
00:09:07,297 --> 00:09:11,033
Borrowed? Borrowed?

132
00:09:14,066 --> 00:09:18,891
Wow, this is the beginning of debt hell, isn't it?

133
00:09:20,792 --> 00:09:26,231
What about the letter? Huh? Ah, I threw that away.

134
00:09:26,231 --> 00:09:31,033
Huh? Promise me that you'll pay it back properly, right?

135
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:32,693
(Sakura) You don't bring money very often.

136
00:09:32,693 --> 00:09:36,924
It's my fault, I had to wait quite a while.

137
00:09:36,924 --> 00:09:38,594
But... if I leave it at home

138
00:09:38,594 --> 00:09:40,792
I might see my mom.

139
00:09:40,792 --> 00:09:44,033
I feel like I just threw it away anyway.

140
00:09:45,792 --> 00:09:49,396
(Sakura) Taro hasn't come to school at all lately...

141
00:09:50,825 --> 00:09:54,330
He's lame and boring.

142
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:57,000
Well, if you think about it, what were you talking about?

143
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:01,099
I can't remember much, but... he's a good guy.

144
00:10:03,132 --> 00:10:07,528
(Sakura) In order to protect your friend, I lost my friend.

145
00:10:07,528 --> 00:10:18,231
♬〜

146
00:10:18,231 --> 00:10:22,594
(Hiroshi) Ah... you came?

147
00:10:22,594 --> 00:10:26,726
Mom, I'm going to the store.

148
00:10:30,693 --> 00:10:32,363
what?

149
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:41,363
Dad, why...

150
00:10:43,363 --> 00:10:46,858
yeah?

151
00:10:46,858 --> 00:10:52,660
You said, ``There was another person on the roof.''

152
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:56,165
That...

153
00:10:56,165 --> 00:11:00,924
So why did you say "I haven't seen it after all"...

154
00:11:07,495 --> 00:11:11,297
I had many dreams

155
00:11:13,495 --> 00:11:18,792
I'm good friends with mom and Sakura...

156
00:11:18,792 --> 00:11:25,330
A good husband...a good father...

157
00:11:25,330 --> 00:11:30,066
But the dream was just a dream and it wasn't real

158
00:11:33,396 --> 00:11:36,495
There's nothing that's not true

159
00:11:40,165 --> 00:11:42,033
Sorry

160
00:11:44,264 --> 00:11:48,726
(Hiroshi) It's okay if you don't come every day anymore.

161
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:55,825
There are so many things you can only do when you're 16 years old.

162
00:11:57,957 --> 00:12:01,627
(Hiroshi) If you don't like it, you can run away.

163
00:12:24,231 --> 00:12:37,858
♬〜

164
00:12:37,858 --> 00:12:41,561
(Sae) Wait, what? Daddy don't leave me alone

165
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:44,528
So, should I have leaked it in the pee room?

166
00:12:44,528 --> 00:12:47,330
Ah... I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

167
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:49,693
Ah, that's right, you can come on Sunday morning, right?

168
00:12:49,693 --> 00:12:51,363
(Sakura) Huh?

169
00:12:51,363 --> 00:12:53,165
(Sae) Dad's rehabilitation is starting.

170
00:12:53,165 --> 00:12:55,198
Mom, I was with the lawyer the other Sunday...

171
00:12:55,198 --> 00:12:58,462
Look, I have to talk about some formalities.

172
00:12:58,462 --> 00:13:03,297
I can't do it on Sunday because I have plans, huh?

173
00:13:03,297 --> 00:13:05,528
Dad, I said, "You don't have to come."

174
00:13:05,528 --> 00:13:08,396
Well, that's what daddy says. Take care of you.

175
00:13:08,396 --> 00:13:12,165
So who is Mom caring about?

176
00:13:12,165 --> 00:13:14,957
Huh? forever like that

177
00:13:14,957 --> 00:13:19,363
My loving wife looked like a mother, even though I was so ready to divorce her.

178
00:13:19,363 --> 00:13:23,000
Don't worry about it!

179
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:26,198
It's not coming, so don't say weird things

180
00:13:26,198 --> 00:13:31,000
Now is the time when we need to work together as a family.

181
00:13:33,528 --> 00:13:35,198
(Sae) Sakura!

182
00:13:36,792 --> 00:13:40,726
(Sae) This... what is this!? Wait... wait! Hey!

183
00:13:40,726 --> 00:13:43,693
(Nurse) Ms. Kondo, your husband will have to see a doctor.

184
00:13:43,693 --> 00:13:46,198
(Sae) Ah...

185
00:13:46,198 --> 00:13:47,858
(sigh)

186
00:13:47,858 --> 00:13:59,858
♬〜

187
00:14:10,528 --> 00:14:12,198
(footsteps)

188
00:14:12,198 --> 00:14:15,528
(Sound of door opening and closing)

189
00:14:15,528 --> 00:14:17,198
Taro?

190
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,000
Where are you going?

191
00:14:23,165 --> 00:14:25,000
Taro wait

192
00:14:27,066 --> 00:14:32,627
Well then, please?

193
00:14:32,627 --> 00:14:37,429
I'll wait and tell you where you've been.

194
00:14:38,891 --> 00:14:41,957
(Taro) What were you going to talk about when you got back?

195
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:53,660
You don't need to worry anymore, everything will be fine

196
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,198
(Uchimura) Eh, who are you?

197
00:15:10,198 --> 00:15:13,627
(Endo) Detective Uchimura, what do you think?

198
00:15:13,627 --> 00:15:17,132
No, no, no, it just came into my field of vision.

199
00:15:17,132 --> 00:15:21,165
My wife died 10 years ago

200
00:15:21,165 --> 00:15:23,330
Suicide?

201
00:15:23,330 --> 00:15:25,924
Let's go...

202
00:15:28,528 --> 00:15:32,132
(Kanda) Mr. Endo, I'm sorry.

203
00:15:32,132 --> 00:15:34,693
Accompanying a lost child at night

204
00:15:34,693 --> 00:15:37,957
No... Is that person a well-protected person?

205
00:15:37,957 --> 00:15:39,627
(Kanda) No, me too that day.

206
00:15:39,627 --> 00:15:42,165
I was just asked by the regional department that there were not enough people.

207
00:15:42,165 --> 00:15:45,363
I don't know much about it, but it's true.

208
00:15:45,363 --> 00:15:48,033
(Kanda) Ah, then please excuse me.

209
00:15:53,231 --> 00:15:55,561
Kanda-san yes

210
00:15:55,561 --> 00:15:59,000
Who in the regional division asked you to do it? (Kanda) Huh?

211
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,132
I would like to know that person's contact information.

212
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,066
Hmm...

213
00:16:55,330 --> 00:17:15,396
♬〜

214
00:17:15,396 --> 00:17:17,165
♬〜

215
00:17:17,165 --> 00:17:20,660
Welcome, it's early, so please start over here.

216
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:22,759
I bought some alcohol just in case.

217
00:17:22,759 --> 00:17:27,429
Thank you. I also ordered sushi, but it hasn't arrived yet.

218
00:17:27,429 --> 00:17:31,132
Hehe... haha?

219
00:17:31,132 --> 00:17:38,528
No... at first I thought they broke the glass and came in, haha.

220
00:17:38,528 --> 00:17:40,198
sorry

221
00:17:46,297 --> 00:17:51,594
"It's pretty expensive and cute", huh?

222
00:17:51,594 --> 00:17:56,858
I wish I had gotten it properly so I could have brought it with me.

223
00:17:56,858 --> 00:18:01,165
There's a festival later, please.

224
00:18:01,165 --> 00:18:21,165
♬〜

225
00:18:21,165 --> 00:18:41,165
♬〜

226
00:18:41,165 --> 00:18:46,165
♬〜

227
00:18:46,165 --> 00:18:47,825
Are you okay?

228
00:18:48,825 --> 00:18:52,462
Ah... sorry

229
00:18:52,462 --> 00:18:59,627
Wow, that's quite a bit like that.

230
00:19:02,495 --> 00:19:04,528
No, something...

231
00:19:04,528 --> 00:19:09,957
I thought I was a bit more of a dry person.

232
00:19:09,957 --> 00:19:15,825
I don't have such feelings about my parents' home or anything like that.

233
00:19:15,825 --> 00:19:19,099
Even when my father died

234
00:19:19,099 --> 00:19:21,396
Well, there's also the fact that it was small.

235
00:19:21,396 --> 00:19:23,858
I don't really remember it.

236
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:28,693
But that's...

237
00:19:28,693 --> 00:19:32,066
It's because your mother was there.

238
00:19:32,066 --> 00:19:37,099
Because my mom made sure I didn't feel lonely...

239
00:19:44,462 --> 00:19:48,231
How was it there? Huh?

240
00:19:48,231 --> 00:19:50,066
No, look, dad.

241
00:19:50,066 --> 00:19:52,924
When I was little, they told me that I was dead.

242
00:19:57,561 --> 00:20:01,561
Ah, sorry, I heard something strange.

243
00:20:01,561 --> 00:20:04,891
No, not at all

244
00:20:04,891 --> 00:20:11,000
I don't really remember much.

245
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,693
I see, sorry

246
00:20:13,693 --> 00:20:15,792
I really mean it

247
00:20:17,792 --> 00:20:23,627
Taro-kun, are you okay after that? Ah... yeah

248
00:20:23,627 --> 00:20:26,132
Hasn't something changed with your mother?

249
00:20:26,132 --> 00:20:29,594
Huh? sorry…

250
00:20:29,594 --> 00:20:31,660
I'm sorry, I'm listening to so many unnecessary things. I'm sorry.

251
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:33,330
Don't apologize, really

252
00:20:33,330 --> 00:20:41,165
But I guess I'm just not good at sensing distance.

253
00:20:41,165 --> 00:20:43,165
I guess you're being too spoiled

254
00:20:43,165 --> 00:20:45,561
It's not like I'm waving it around.

255
00:20:45,561 --> 00:20:49,099
But like the other day at Kenken.

256
00:20:49,099 --> 00:20:54,099
Since then, I've been thinking that I did something unnecessary.

257
00:20:54,099 --> 00:20:56,693
There were probably things that only the two of us could understand.

258
00:20:56,693 --> 00:20:59,660
That's enough, because there really isn't anything like that.

259
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:04,264
Oh, and that's Gyoza Day, huh?

260
00:21:04,264 --> 00:21:07,693
The next morning, you went home in silence.

261
00:21:07,693 --> 00:21:11,198
I kept asking "why?"

262
00:21:11,198 --> 00:21:16,594
No, but he's a normal adult and has various circumstances.

263
00:21:16,594 --> 00:21:20,396
I guess it's a good nuisance for me to hang out with.

264
00:21:20,396 --> 00:21:23,297
What are you saying?

265
00:21:26,462 --> 00:21:30,693
In the same way, about your mother too.

266
00:21:30,693 --> 00:21:35,264
In the end, I guess he was just doing what was convenient for him.

267
00:21:39,330 --> 00:21:46,693
Just before we closed the store, my mom had cataract surgery.

268
00:21:46,693 --> 00:21:51,693
There was a time when I got stuck on the way home.

269
00:21:51,693 --> 00:21:53,363
Huh?

270
00:21:54,693 --> 00:21:59,330
I felt sorry for not being able to go home alone.

271
00:21:59,330 --> 00:22:02,264
I didn't know that at the time either.

272
00:22:02,264 --> 00:22:07,099
I heard it from my uncle later.

273
00:22:07,099 --> 00:22:13,198
I wonder what it is...like how my mother feels.

274
00:22:13,198 --> 00:22:16,825
I didn't want to hear that.

275
00:22:19,198 --> 00:22:25,429
The more I think about it, the more I think of it.

276
00:22:25,429 --> 00:22:28,495
Actually, there were a few

277
00:22:29,759 --> 00:22:33,759
No, I didn't think I was going to die.

278
00:22:33,759 --> 00:22:36,231
It's really true though

279
00:22:39,561 --> 00:22:46,429
But that kind of mother's weakness is

280
00:22:46,429 --> 00:22:51,693
I don't want to admit the things I've been ignoring...

281
00:22:51,693 --> 00:22:56,660
That's why my mother committed suicide...

282
00:23:00,495 --> 00:23:06,033
(sob)

283
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:10,363
I didn't want to admit it for a long time...

284
00:23:10,363 --> 00:23:23,726
♬〜

285
00:23:23,726 --> 00:23:26,033
ah…

286
00:23:28,231 --> 00:23:30,561
(TV) "It smells really bad, so sleep on the floor!"

287
00:23:30,561 --> 00:23:32,825
``I feel sorry for mom, don't you?''

288
00:23:32,825 --> 00:23:34,495
gently and softly

289
00:23:34,495 --> 00:23:36,594
By communicating using stuffed animals

290
00:23:36,594 --> 00:23:40,429
I'm sorry, I understand, in a blunt manner.

291
00:23:40,429 --> 00:23:43,297
I can say what I want to say...”

292
00:23:43,297 --> 00:24:03,297
♬〜

293
00:24:03,297 --> 00:24:23,297
♬〜

294
00:24:23,297 --> 00:24:39,462
♬〜

295
00:24:39,462 --> 00:24:46,198
No, it was here.

296
00:24:46,198 --> 00:24:47,858
ah…

297
00:24:47,858 --> 00:24:56,264
♬〜

298
00:24:56,264 --> 00:24:58,858
(Misato) See you next time?

299
00:25:00,891 --> 00:25:02,561
(Misato) Hey

300
00:25:02,561 --> 00:25:15,759
♬〜

301
00:25:15,759 --> 00:25:18,132
Hmm...

302
00:25:18,132 --> 00:25:27,825
♬〜

303
00:25:27,825 --> 00:25:29,858
(Tsukaji) “I was allowed to see it.

304
00:25:29,858 --> 00:25:31,627
I thought he was a child with a bad personality.”

305
00:25:31,627 --> 00:25:34,759
(sigh)

306
00:25:34,759 --> 00:25:37,726
"When Tsukaji-san says that, I get that impression."

307
00:25:37,726 --> 00:25:40,825
(Tsukaji) “Well, there are a lot of videos that show people acting out that.”

308
00:25:40,825 --> 00:25:44,330
“But the thing about that is that it’s pretty obvious…”

309
00:25:44,330 --> 00:25:59,627
♬〜

310
00:25:59,627 --> 00:26:01,627
(notification sound)

311
00:26:01,627 --> 00:26:05,759
(Misato) Yes, yes, what is it?

312
00:26:06,891 --> 00:26:08,561
yeah?

313
00:26:20,693 --> 00:26:22,363
(notification sound)

314
00:26:49,363 --> 00:26:53,396
(sound of breathing)

315
00:26:53,396 --> 00:27:01,297
Why couldn't you be more kind?

316
00:27:01,297 --> 00:27:08,429
(sob)

317
00:27:08,429 --> 00:27:12,627
Hehe... what?

318
00:27:12,627 --> 00:27:16,726
Did your body move on its own again?

319
00:27:16,726 --> 00:27:18,396
No, that's not true.

320
00:27:30,528 --> 00:27:35,231
I don't understand anything, Mio-chan.

321
00:27:35,231 --> 00:27:38,231
Huh?

322
00:27:38,231 --> 00:27:43,561
I don't understand your mother's feelings at all.

323
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:47,561
Huh?

324
00:27:47,561 --> 00:27:52,825
Mio-chan, think a lot like that.

325
00:27:52,825 --> 00:27:56,462
Think about people's feelings...

326
00:27:58,330 --> 00:28:02,924
But in the end, what does the other person think?

327
00:28:02,924 --> 00:28:07,462
I don't know.

328
00:28:07,462 --> 00:28:09,528
Maybe so...

329
00:28:09,528 --> 00:28:11,726
Because Mio-chan...

330
00:28:13,396 --> 00:28:17,528
You don't even understand me at all

331
00:28:17,528 --> 00:28:20,462
Huh?

332
00:28:20,462 --> 00:28:23,594
You don't understand me at all

333
00:28:28,396 --> 00:28:34,528
Actually it's me...

334
00:28:42,297 --> 00:28:46,429
Haha hehe

335
00:28:46,429 --> 00:28:51,495
You really don't understand anymore, Mio-chan.

336
00:28:51,495 --> 00:28:54,099
Huh? What?

337
00:28:59,825 --> 00:29:04,297
Have you ever thought that you are being manipulated or that you are a nuisance?

338
00:29:04,297 --> 00:29:06,363
Not once

339
00:29:08,297 --> 00:29:12,462
It's been fun ever since I met Mio-chan

340
00:29:15,924 --> 00:29:19,297
It's my first time making friends like this too.

341
00:29:24,429 --> 00:29:31,396
So... from now on, we'll always be together...

342
00:29:34,561 --> 00:29:36,957
I want to be friends

343
00:29:41,033 --> 00:29:44,825
Because that's my truth

344
00:29:52,198 --> 00:29:56,033
Hehe... that's creepy

345
00:29:56,033 --> 00:30:00,957
Hehehehe, it's creepy, but it's definitely a little bit creepy.

346
00:30:03,693 --> 00:30:05,429
thank you

347
00:30:07,429 --> 00:30:09,099
Yeah

348
00:30:10,858 --> 00:30:15,726
Well then, shall we drink? It's too late for sushi.

349
00:30:16,726 --> 00:30:21,858
Ah, salty, huh?

350
00:30:21,858 --> 00:30:28,264
``If the gift is really salted fish, please give it to me.''

351
00:30:28,264 --> 00:30:31,693
The last words I heard directly from my mother

352
00:30:31,693 --> 00:30:33,594
Huh?

353
00:30:33,594 --> 00:30:39,165
You loved the delicious squid seafood special salted fish, didn't you, Mom?

354
00:30:39,165 --> 00:30:41,561
Ah, that convenience store doesn't have it.

355
00:30:41,561 --> 00:30:43,627
It's in the mall over there.

356
00:30:43,627 --> 00:30:45,792
Ah, I should have bought it.

357
00:30:45,792 --> 00:30:51,660
So, do you want to go shopping? No, it's fine, it's far away

358
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:53,660
Ah... Huh?

359
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:57,759
I'm asking you a little favor...

360
00:30:59,957 --> 00:31:03,198
I wanted to try it once.

361
00:31:03,198 --> 00:31:08,792
Besides, these scissors aren't used anymore either.

362
00:31:08,792 --> 00:31:15,660
So... yes, please stay still.

363
00:31:15,660 --> 00:31:17,330
Wait a minute, wait a minute, wait a minute!

364
00:31:17,330 --> 00:31:19,627
No, no, no, it's definitely okay right now

365
00:31:19,627 --> 00:31:21,297
No, no, no...

366
00:31:21,297 --> 00:31:22,957
Whoa whoa

367
00:31:26,231 --> 00:31:27,891
Ah...

368
00:31:30,594 --> 00:31:33,330
Huh? Wait a minute?

369
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:36,330
Huh? Eh...

370
00:31:36,330 --> 00:31:38,033
It’s a kappa! No, no, no, no...

371
00:31:38,033 --> 00:31:40,495
On-eyebrows are cute, huh?

372
00:31:40,495 --> 00:31:42,759
No, I'm sorry, I'm not apologizing!

373
00:31:42,759 --> 00:31:45,132
Sorry, wait a minute, eh?

374
00:31:45,132 --> 00:31:46,858
No, no, it's cute, it's the worst!

375
00:31:46,858 --> 00:31:49,033
Really cute (sound of door opening)

376
00:31:50,594 --> 00:31:52,594
Huh? (Sakuma) Huh...

377
00:31:52,594 --> 00:31:56,462
Huh... what happened?

378
00:31:56,462 --> 00:32:01,198
I heard that you were moving, so...

379
00:32:03,297 --> 00:32:07,132
Incense for your mother

380
00:32:07,132 --> 00:32:09,660
Can I raise it?

381
00:32:09,660 --> 00:32:11,495
Huh?

382
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,000
(bell)

383
00:32:26,693 --> 00:32:29,726
thank you

384
00:32:29,726 --> 00:32:32,363
Actually, the funeral will also be held at this house.

385
00:32:32,363 --> 00:32:34,660
I wanted to do it for you.

386
00:32:34,660 --> 00:32:37,297
I couldn't do it due to various reasons.

387
00:32:37,297 --> 00:32:41,165
In the end, I had to move...

388
00:32:41,165 --> 00:32:45,726
So I'm really happy

389
00:32:51,594 --> 00:32:56,594
So I... did you come by car?

390
00:32:56,594 --> 00:33:01,000
Huh? Yeah

391
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:04,132
Can you lend me your car?

392
00:33:04,132 --> 00:33:07,792
The sushi will arrive, so I'll stay home for a while.

393
00:33:07,792 --> 00:33:11,165
Huh? Wait, what?

394
00:33:11,165 --> 00:33:16,231
Shall we go buy some salted fish?

395
00:33:18,627 --> 00:33:21,957
Hehe... yeah

396
00:33:24,066 --> 00:33:25,726
key

397
00:33:25,726 --> 00:33:27,396
Ah...

398
00:33:29,858 --> 00:33:31,528
let's go

399
00:33:33,594 --> 00:33:41,066
Yes, yes, then I'll take it down. 1 2 of 3

400
00:33:43,330 --> 00:33:46,627
(Physical therapist) Are you okay? (Hiroshi) Yes

401
00:33:46,627 --> 00:33:50,858
Ah, sorry, I'm late. How are you doing?

402
00:33:50,858 --> 00:33:54,231
(Physical therapist) I'm about to move to the rehabilitation room.

403
00:33:54,231 --> 00:33:59,231
♬〜

404
00:33:59,231 --> 00:34:02,726
(Sae) Ah, wait... Sakura? (Hiroshi) It's okay.

405
00:34:06,396 --> 00:34:09,759
First... I'll go right away.

406
00:34:11,495 --> 00:34:13,165
(Sae) Sakura!

407
00:34:14,759 --> 00:34:16,429
Sakura says it's okay until noon.

408
00:34:16,429 --> 00:34:19,330
I told you! What was that money the other day?

409
00:34:19,330 --> 00:34:21,000
Do you have money to run away from home?

410
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,165
I'm leaving home, so I won't come home today either.

411
00:34:23,165 --> 00:34:25,396
What do you mean you're not going home? There's nowhere to go, right?

412
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:27,924
Yes, let go!

413
00:34:27,924 --> 00:34:30,000
(Sae) Sakura!

414
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:39,561
♬〜

415
00:34:39,561 --> 00:34:42,297
It's okay, it's really cute

416
00:34:42,297 --> 00:34:44,528
Wait a minute, wait a minute, huh?

417
00:34:48,627 --> 00:34:51,297
Ah, sorry (female), no.

418
00:34:55,660 --> 00:34:58,099
(elevator arrival sound)

419
00:35:03,693 --> 00:35:07,033
Oh, sorry, first...

420
00:35:13,594 --> 00:35:16,693
Haven't you longed for this? When I was a child

421
00:35:16,693 --> 00:35:18,594
Not at all

422
00:35:18,594 --> 00:35:20,924
Well, it's just salted fish, so you don't need it, right?

423
00:35:20,924 --> 00:35:23,924
No, I also want to buy some more alcohol.

424
00:35:23,924 --> 00:35:26,396
There's something strangely childlike about it.

425
00:35:26,396 --> 00:35:29,561
You're as cold as Dracula sometimes.

426
00:35:29,561 --> 00:35:31,231
Is Dracula cold?

427
00:35:31,231 --> 00:35:33,891
Ah, hey, let's go over there next time, that haunted house.

428
00:35:33,891 --> 00:35:36,594
Hey, do you know that? That thing over there is famous...

429
00:35:36,594 --> 00:35:38,495
All I say is "there" and "that"

430
00:35:38,495 --> 00:35:41,594
It's really scary, just over there.

431
00:35:41,594 --> 00:35:44,132
No, I went there once with my mom when I was a kid.

432
00:35:44,132 --> 00:35:48,231
I really cried. Huh? Shall we go together?

433
00:35:48,231 --> 00:35:51,396
Hmm... In that case, it's like a hot spring or something...

434
00:35:51,396 --> 00:35:55,759
Ah, yes, there is a hot spring.

435
00:35:55,759 --> 00:35:58,726
Hey, do you have a hot spring ghost set too?

436
00:35:58,726 --> 00:36:02,759
Ah, okay, okay, that's okay, stay for about one night.

437
00:36:02,759 --> 00:36:05,363
But does this set look like it's bad for your heart?

438
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:07,561
It's okay, right? Let's go. Let's go. When should we do it?

439
00:36:07,561 --> 00:36:09,231
Yeah?

440
00:36:10,231 --> 00:36:12,363
Sorry for bothering to call you.

441
00:36:12,363 --> 00:36:14,033
(Kayoko) No, no, just a little on the phone.

442
00:36:14,033 --> 00:36:15,957
We talked about it, but... uh...

443
00:36:15,957 --> 00:36:18,891
Actually, some strange photos came out (Endo) Huh?

444
00:36:18,891 --> 00:36:21,165
Ah... ah! (Kayoko) It's okay, Dad.

445
00:36:21,165 --> 00:36:26,330
Just show me the photo, okay, okay, okay, okay.

446
00:36:26,330 --> 00:36:29,759
Ah... (Kayoko) Um...

447
00:36:30,858 --> 00:36:34,132
(Sound of door opening and closing)

448
00:36:34,132 --> 00:36:37,231
Welcome back, sushi, yet...

449
00:36:40,132 --> 00:36:42,726
Huh? What are you doing? In the middle of nowhere

450
00:36:42,726 --> 00:36:48,033
No, that... eh... what about you?

451
00:36:48,033 --> 00:36:52,033
Well, no, check one thing, okay?

452
00:36:52,033 --> 00:36:56,957
Were you together? That day with that woman

453
00:36:56,957 --> 00:37:00,495
I didn't write that well in the letter.

454
00:37:03,297 --> 00:37:05,495
I see.

455
00:37:05,495 --> 00:37:09,363
what? Did you think it would be bad if you found out you had an affair?

456
00:37:09,363 --> 00:37:11,429
Then I saw my dad collapse.

457
00:37:11,429 --> 00:37:13,957
I just left it alone and ran away.

458
00:37:15,132 --> 00:37:16,792
(Sakura) Because of you

459
00:37:16,792 --> 00:37:21,066
My family has become a mess

460
00:37:21,066 --> 00:37:23,363
Then that person

461
00:37:23,363 --> 00:37:28,297
He gave me a duplicate key so I could come when I didn't want to go home.

462
00:37:28,297 --> 00:37:31,660
so now i came here

463
00:37:34,396 --> 00:37:36,462
(Taro) What do you mean?

464
00:37:36,462 --> 00:37:46,495
♬〜

465
00:37:46,495 --> 00:37:48,924
What does "escape" mean?

466
00:38:04,462 --> 00:38:06,132
(Sae) Already...

467
00:38:06,132 --> 00:38:18,000
♬〜

468
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,528
The cash registers are all on the first floor, right? Yeah

469
00:38:24,528 --> 00:38:27,000
(elevator arrival sound)

470
00:38:30,330 --> 00:38:32,132
Ah sorry yes

471
00:38:32,132 --> 00:38:34,495
(Female) Thank you very much.

472
00:38:35,561 --> 00:38:39,231
Oh wow, worst of all, I forgot the toilet paper.

473
00:38:39,231 --> 00:38:42,264
Huh? It's very subtle.

474
00:38:42,264 --> 00:38:45,363
Will I be able to hold out until tomorrow?

475
00:38:45,363 --> 00:38:48,726
Mio-chan, you often go to the bathroom after drinking, right?

476
00:38:48,726 --> 00:38:53,198
Is it a problem if you can't wipe your butt?

477
00:38:58,957 --> 00:39:02,099
(elevator arrival sound)

478
00:39:02,099 --> 00:39:05,462
Ah, that! It's inside and out

479
00:39:05,462 --> 00:39:10,165
(Female) Oh no, I'm sorry.

480
00:39:10,165 --> 00:39:14,198
Ah, now that mouth spoke on its own.

481
00:39:14,198 --> 00:39:18,825
Well then, I'll go back to the third floor, and I won't forget to buy anything else, okay?

482
00:39:22,330 --> 00:39:25,462
Did I push it?

483
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:35,627
Pushing Mio's mother's back...

484
00:39:35,627 --> 00:39:38,495
I was the one who pushed it down.

485
00:39:40,231 --> 00:39:43,231
Huh?

486
00:39:43,231 --> 00:39:51,924
You said we met at the station, which is true, but...

487
00:39:51,924 --> 00:39:56,594
Actually, we'll meet again after that...

488
00:39:56,594 --> 00:39:59,561
Find me on the roof...

489
00:40:01,858 --> 00:40:04,825
(Elevator arrival sound) Huh?

490
00:40:20,495 --> 00:40:24,891
Mom was about to jump.

491
00:40:24,891 --> 00:40:29,726
So I decided I had to stop it, so I went up to the roof...

492
00:40:29,726 --> 00:40:33,495
Let's talk for a while and have a beer...

493
00:40:36,165 --> 00:40:41,264
The suicide note... I took it home with me at that time.

494
00:40:41,264 --> 00:40:45,726
So... it didn't come out when we moved.

495
00:40:49,594 --> 00:40:52,825
So...

496
00:40:52,825 --> 00:40:55,033
So I thought I'd go home

497
00:40:55,033 --> 00:40:58,495
Then a pigeon came... and I was surprised...

498
00:40:58,495 --> 00:41:00,165
《(Klaxon)》

499
00:41:00,165 --> 00:41:03,957
Then, at that moment... my hand...

500
00:41:06,099 --> 00:41:11,627
With my hands... Mom's back...

501
00:41:16,264 --> 00:41:22,396
Mio-chan's mother died... It's my fault.

502
00:41:28,891 --> 00:41:31,033
TRUE…

503
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:34,792
I'm really sorry...

504
00:41:34,792 --> 00:41:41,297
♬〜

505
00:41:41,297 --> 00:41:45,858
(Taro) At the time of Mr. Kondo's father's accident.

506
00:41:45,858 --> 00:41:49,231
So Kenken and his sister were there too?

507
00:41:49,231 --> 00:41:55,627
♬〜

508
00:41:55,627 --> 00:41:57,297
《Dream? 》

509
00:41:59,066 --> 00:42:02,825
(Sushi restaurant) Sorry, I brought you some sushi.

510
00:42:06,066 --> 00:42:08,396
What, did you order some sushi?

511
00:42:08,396 --> 00:42:12,000
No... wait a minute.

512
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:18,297
♬〜

513
00:42:18,297 --> 00:42:21,330
Does that mean Kondo-san knows everything?

514
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:34,627
♬〜

515
00:42:34,627 --> 00:42:37,627
(Sushi restaurant) Yes, every time. Do you have a receipt?

516
00:42:37,627 --> 00:42:39,759
Ah, okay, thank you very much

517
00:42:39,759 --> 00:42:42,363
(Sushi restaurant) Well then, please again.

518
00:42:42,363 --> 00:42:44,033
Kenken!

519
00:42:47,462 --> 00:42:50,495
Is Yume Nakata here?

520
00:42:52,132 --> 00:42:55,726
(Taro) Huh? I'm going to do some shopping now.

521
00:42:55,726 --> 00:42:59,891
Well, I just had something to say to you.

522
00:42:59,891 --> 00:43:02,594
Eh...

523
00:43:02,594 --> 00:43:05,495
(Endo) This is you, right?

524
00:43:05,495 --> 00:43:09,726
♬〜

525
00:43:09,726 --> 00:43:13,462
(cell phone vibration sound)

526
00:43:13,462 --> 00:43:15,132
Ah, that...

527
00:43:15,132 --> 00:43:17,726
(Endo) Could you please accompany me to the police station?

528
00:43:17,726 --> 00:43:23,957
♬〜

529
00:43:23,957 --> 00:43:26,396
I've been meaning to say this for a long time...

530
00:43:29,957 --> 00:43:32,495
But I just couldn't say it

531
00:43:35,759 --> 00:43:40,363
With Mio-chan...

532
00:43:40,363 --> 00:43:45,396
Together forever...

533
00:43:45,396 --> 00:43:47,825
I want to be friends...

534
00:43:52,726 --> 00:43:59,528
I'm really... sorry.

535
00:44:03,330 --> 00:44:06,033
What is a friend?

536
00:44:13,429 --> 00:44:15,627
Mio-chan...

537
00:44:15,627 --> 00:44:18,429
(impact sound)

538
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:29,726
(alarm sound)

539
00:44:29,726 --> 00:44:32,132
Mio-chan... Ah!

540
00:44:32,132 --> 00:44:37,495
(alarm sound)

541
00:44:39,330 --> 00:44:42,363
People are dying because of me, who I don't want to see anymore.

542
00:44:42,363 --> 00:44:44,033
I know that!

543
00:44:44,033 --> 00:44:47,528
If my sister tries hard, everything will go wrong.

544
00:44:47,528 --> 00:44:50,429
I want to make amends even a little...

545
00:44:50,429 --> 00:44:53,000
Even so, Yume always had the suicide note.
